Annotation.note:
A family of systems with symmetry group $C_3$ and common zero
$(1,1,1)$ with $n&gt;2$. 


The ideal generated by these polynomials has dimension 0 and
multiplicity $n^3$, since the polynomials form a deglex. Gr\&quot;obner
basis.

It can be generated by the following code:
\begin{verbatim}
#requires System=Maple
polys:=[
  x^n + y*z - 2,
  y^n + z*x - 2,
  z^n + x*y - 2];

vars:=[x,y,z];
\end{verbatim}

\begin{keywords}
discrete symmetries
\end{keywords}
